# Architecture Rules

- Follow package-by-feature.
- Keep controllers thin.
- Business logic belongs in services/use-case classes.
- Domain logic must not depend on transport DTOs.
- Infrastructure concerns must stay isolated.
- Avoid creating extra layers like Manager/Facade/Helper unless justified.
- Prefer constructor injection only.
- No field injection.
- No circular package dependencies.
- Before creating a new class, check whether an existing class should be extended.
